<@U3ZFEAPSP|oliver> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/oliver/F4ZB0GN4F/earth_force_refresh.apk|earth_force_refresh.apk>

Updated build to test before cutting a release candidate to send over to Google.
This has handling that after un unhandled crash will force the Earth images to reload and will upload via the GA tags which image asset it crashed on. Forcing it to crash worked correctly (Midori & Summer, going into the BitmapRegionLoader and forcing a RuntimeError will do it) in reloading the Earth images and triggering a GA message so we can get some more details.
This build is the one that doesn’t force runtime errors :slightly_smiling_face: So running it should work as normal (with the regular slideslow rate, not the sped up version).
Let me know if you run into any issues, I’ve been running it since heading out and it seems ok
